INT. OFFICE - NIGHT

The room is lit only by a desk lamp. PRIYA sits across from her old mentor, VICTOR.

VICTOR
(quietly)
You didn't have to come.

PRIYA
(beat)
Yes, I did.

VICTOR
(leaning back, exhausted)
Then let's not waste the evening on pleasantries.

PRIYA
(a small laugh)
(then, serious)
Tell me what happened.

Victor pours two glasses of water. He doesn't touch his.

VICTOR
(after a long pause)
It started three weeks ago.
